{"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/threadinit(vtable:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"If you use GLib from more than one thread, you must initialize the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"thread system by calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threadInit","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"vtable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since version 2.24, calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":" multiple times is allowed,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"but nothing happens except for the first call."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since version 2.32, GLib does not support custom thread implementations","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"anymore and the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vtable"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter is ignored and you should pass "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":":","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" note","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must not be called directly or indirectly in a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"callback from GLib. Also no mutexes may be currently locked","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"while calling "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":":","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" note"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" in your program, you have to link with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the libraries that the command "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pkg-config --libs gthread-2.0"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"outputs. This is not the case for all the other thread-related"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions of GLib. Those can be used without having to link"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with the thread libraries.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"thread_init is deprecated:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This function is no longer necessary. The GLib"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threading system is automatically initialized at the start","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of your program."}]}]}],"metadata":{"platforms":[],"title":"threadInit(vtable:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib10threadInit6vtableySvSg_tF","roleHeading":"Function","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threadInit","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"vtable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"func"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/threadInit(vtable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation